Police officers have killed three suspects after they had allegedly robbed a man gunpoint.
Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said in a statement that on Monday at 9am, the victim had gone to deposit money at a bank in Dalton when he had been approached by four armed suspects.
"They held him up and stole an undisclosed amount of cash. They fled in an awaiting getaway vehicle. The police were alerted and the Pietermaritzburg Response Unit, Task Force and Dalton SAPS began tracing the vehicle."
READ: Suspect killed by police in shootout
He said it had been spotted in the vicinity of Dalton. 
"When the suspects saw the police, they abandoned their vehicle and fled to the sugarcane fields while shooting at police. One suspect died at the scene during the shootout, two died en route to hospital, one managed to flee the scene. Police are still searching for him."
READ: Suspects arrested after shootout with police
He said that two pistols, a revolver, two AK47 rifles and cash taken during the robbery were also recovered. 
"The vehicle was hijacked in Prestbury last October."

